# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260323-103001-5842
## Findings
1. [P2] Tile-mode stepper buttons remain below 44px touch target — In [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L280) and [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L290), the tile-mode decrement/increment buttons still use `className="w-8 h-8 ..."`, so each control is 32x32px instead of the required 44x44px minimum. This leaves the grid-mode stepper harder to tap on mobile and inconsistent with the already-fixed list-mode stepper. FIX: change only the tile-mode `Minus` and `Plus` stepper buttons in `renderTileCard()` from `w-8 h-8` to at least `w-11 h-11`, keeping the existing `w-4 h-4` icon sizes and leaving list mode plus the initial add button unchanged.
2. [P3] Checkout quantity aria-labels are still hardcoded in English — In [CheckoutView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CheckoutView.jsx#L60) and [CheckoutView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CheckoutView.jsx#L64), the quantity buttons still use `aria-label="Decrease"` and `aria-label="Increase"`. That bypasses the existing i18n path in this component and leaves assistive text untranslated. FIX: replace them with `aria-label={t('cart.decrease', 'Уменьшить')}` and `aria-label={t('cart.increase', 'Увеличить')}` without changing button behavior or styling.
3. [P2] Discounted price text still uses the badge color instead of the brand color — In [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L126) and [MenuView.jsx](/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu%20AI%20Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx#L239), the discounted price `<span>` still uses `partner?.discount_color || '#C92A2A'`, matching the sale badge color. That collapses two different visual roles into the same color and does not implement the requested hierarchy where the payable price follows `partner.primary_color`. FIX: keep the badge background on `partner.discount_color`, but change both discounted price spans to `style={{ color: primaryColor }}` and leave the crossed-out original price styling untouched.

## Summary
Total: 3 findings (0 P0, 0 P1, 2 P2, 1 P3)

